Citation.sTitle: P-rho-T Measurements of Imidazolium-Based Ionic Liquids
Citation.sAbstract: Experimental density measurements are reported, and the derived thermodynamic properties, such as the isothermal  compressibility, the isobaric expansivity, and the thermal pressure coefficient are presented as Supporting  Information for several imidazolium-based ionic liquids (ILs), namely, 1-ethyl-3-methyl-imidazolium bis-  (trifluoromethylsulfonyl)imide [C2mim][NTf2], 1-heptyl-3-methyl-imidazolium bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl)imide  [C7mim][NTf2], 1-octyl-3-methyl-imidazolium bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl)imide [C8mim][NTf2], 1-ethyl-3-methylimidazolium  tetrafluoroborate [C2mim][BF4], and 1-butyl-3-methyl-imidazolium tricyanomethane [C4mim][C(CN)3]  in the pressure (0.10 less than p/MPa less than 30.00) and temperature (293.15 less than T/K less than 393.15) domains. These ILs were  chosen to provide an understanding of the influence of the cation alkyl chain length and the anion influence on  the properties under study. Experimental densities are correlated with the Tait equation with an average absolute  deviation (AAD) less than 0.04 %. Experimental densities are in good agreement with the densities obtained by  some recent predictive methods proposed in the literature.
